8th Ring (Indoor/Outdoor, Doable mostly solo, pretty easy)<br>
Amulet of Necropotence (Indoor/Outdoor, best imo, works from inventory, no stacking issues, etc)<br>
Acumen Mask (Indoor/Outdoor, Works from inventory, but the perspective change is a bit disorienting. This is the easiest indoor/outdoor/inventory insta for wizards that I'm aware of.)<br>
Jboots (outdoor only, works from inventory. Has some useful stacking features with certain AEs that affect movement)<br>
<br>
These aren't instant, but are fast enough to be used in some situations:<br>
<br>
Skyshrine/Kael/Thurg boots (must target, some stacking issues)<br>
Skyshrine/Kael/Thurg bracer (pretty decent, no need to target, etc)<br>
<br>
<br>
If you don't have time/money to pick up anything else, do the quest for an Acumen Mask, and if you can't take the perspective change, there's a wide variety of shaman potions that will work for a relatively small amount of coin. Go for the cheaper ones, and a couple or three 10-packs will get you through most fights with dispelling ae-rs.<br>
<br>
~Celebairn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=motoeisen>MotoEisen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/03 3:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Instant click items</span><hr size=1> I use the Eye of Innoruuk - usable from inventory, indoor/outdoor, cheap (3-5k usually on Nameless) and even has a semi-useful effect. Amulet of Necropotence is also good but hard to come by IMO. <p>--<br>
